# repo-summary-prompt

GitHub repo analysis tool: TypeScript CLI + Hono web server + vanilla JS frontend.

## Architecture

- `src/index.ts` — CLI entry point; fetches data in parallel, emits `@@METRICS@@` JSON to stderr, prints Markdown prompt to stdout
- `src/api.ts` — typed fetch helpers for GitHub stats API + package registries (NPM, PyPI, Cargo, Homebrew)
- `src/summarize.ts` — metric analysis (time-series, rates, momentum)
- `src/prompt.ts` — assembles summaries into structured Markdown
- `ui/server.mjs` — Hono SSE server; spawns CLI as child process
- `ui/main.js` — vanilla JS frontend; renders metric cards and fetch tracker

## Rules

- ESM project: import local `.ts` files with `.js` extension
- Always run `node ui/server.mjs` from the **project root** (not from `ui/`)
- No frontend framework — keep `ui/main.js` as vanilla JS
- New data sources must verify the `repository` field links back to the GitHub repo
- Use `dev.sh` for local development (start / stop / restart)

## Dev commands

```bash
./dev.sh              # start
./dev.sh restart      # restart
npx tsx src/index.ts <owner/repo>  # CLI only
npx tsc --noEmit      # type-check
```
